  <main>
    <h1>Building a Personal Knowledge Model</h1>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>This programme enables delegates to construct a structured personal knowledge model integrating language models, domain-specific publications, and their own professional output. The emphasis is on disciplined knowledge representation rather than tool familiarity.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Who It Is For</h2>
      <p>Professionals operating in analytically demanding roles who need to manage:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Large volumes of technical documentation</li>
        <li>Cross-domain synthesis</li>
        <li>Iterative analytical development</li>
        <li>Long-term intellectual capital</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>What Delegates Produce</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>A formalised personal knowledge architecture</li>
        <li>A reproducible workflow integrating language models and primary sources</li>
        <li>A structured archive of analytical output</li>
        <li>A documented refinement process for ongoing development</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Core Themes</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Knowledge representation and abstraction</li>
        <li>Structured note-taking and retrieval systems</li>
        <li>Language model augmentation strategies</li>
        <li>Versioned intellectual development</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <p><a href="../programmes.html">Back to all programmes</a></p>
